    • Field Detail

      • autorange

        @Option
public AxisOptions.AutoRangeEnum autorange
        Determines whether or not the range of this axis is computed in relation to the input data. Defaults to TRUE.

      • categoryorder

        @Option
public AxisOptions.CategoryOrderEnum categoryorder
        Specifies the ordering logic for the case of categorical variables. By default, plotly uses "trace", which specifies the order that is present in the data supplied.

      • categoryarray

        @Option
public String[] categoryarray
        The order in which categories on this axis appear. Only has an effect if "categoryorder" is set to "array". Used with "categoryorder".

      • color

        @Option
public String color
        Default for all colors associated with this axis all at once: line, font, tick, and grid colors. Grid color is lightened by blending this with the plot background Individual pieces can override this. Default is "#444".

      • dtick

        @Option
public Integer dtick
        The stride between grid lines along the axis. Defaults to 1.

      • exponentformat

        @Option
public ExponentFormatEnum exponentformat
        Determines a formatting rule for the tick exponents.

      • fixedrange

        @Option
public Boolean fixedrange
        Determines whether or not this axis is zoom-able. If true, then zoom is disabled.

      • gridcolor

        @Option
public String gridcolor
        The grid line color.

      • gridwidth

        @Option
public Integer gridwidth
        The width (in px) of the grid line. Defaults to 1.

      • linecolor

        @Option
public String linecolor
        The axis line color. Defaults to "#444".

      • linewidth

        @Option
public Integer linewidth
        The width (in px) of the axis line. Defaults to 1.

      • nticks

        @Option
public Integer nticks
        The maximum number of ticks for the particular axis. The actual number of ticks will be chosen automatically to be less than or equal to "nticks". Has an effect only if "tickmode" is set to "auto".

      • range

        @Option
public Object[] range
        The range of this axis. If the axis "type" is "log", then you must take the log of your desired range (e.g. to set the range from 1 to 100, set the range from 0 to 2). If the axis "type" is "date", it should be date strings, like date data, though Date objects and unix milliseconds will be accepted and converted to strings. If the axis "type" is "category", it should be numbers, using the scale where each category is assigned a serial number from zero in the order it appears.

      • rangemode

        @Option
public AxisOptions.RangeModeEnum rangemode
        Determines the range mode. Defaults to NORMAL.

      • separatethousands

        @Option
public Boolean separatethousands
        If true, even 4-digit integers are separated.

      • showexponent

        @Option
public ShowTickEnum showexponent
        Controls when to display exponent.

      • showgrid

        @Option
public Boolean showgrid
        Determines whether or not grid lines are drawn. If true (the default), the grid lines are drawn at every tick mark.

      • showline

        @Option
public Boolean showline
        Determines whether or not a line bounding this axis is drawn.

      • showticklabels

        @Option
public AxisOptions.ShowTickLabelsEnum showticklabels
        Determines whether axis labels are drawn on the low side, the high side, both, or neither side of the axis. Defaults to START.

      • showtickprefix

        @Option
public ShowTickEnum showtickprefix
        How to display tick label prefix.

      • showticksuffix

        @Option
public ShowTickEnum showticksuffix
        How to display a tick label suffix.

      • tick0

        @Option
public Integer tick0
        The starting index of grid lines along the axis. Defaults to 0.

      • tickangle

        @Option
public String tickangle
        The angle of the tick labels with respect to the horizontal. For example, a "tickangle" of -90 draws the tick labels vertically. Defaults to "auto".

      • tickfont

        @Option
public final FontOptions tickfont
        The tick font.

      • tickformat

        @Option
public String tickformat
        The tick label formatting rule using d3 formatting mini-languages which are very similar to those in Python. We add one item to d3's date formatter: "%{n}f" for fractional seconds with n digits. For example, "2016-10-13 09:15:23.456" with tickformat "%H~%M~%S.%2f" would display "09~15~23.46"

      • tickformatstops_dtickrange

        @Option(value="tickformatstops.dtickrange")
public Double[] tickformatstops_dtickrange
        Range ["min", "max"], where "min", "max" - dtick values which describe some zoom level, it is possible to omit "min" or "max" value by passing "null".

      • tickformatstops_value

        @Option(value="tickformatstops.value")
public String tickformatstops_value
        dtickformat for described zoom level, the same as "tickformat".

      • tickmode

        @Option
public TickModeEnum tickmode
        The tick mode for the axis.

      • tickprefix

        @Option
public String tickprefix
        Tick label prefix.

      • ticksuffix

        @Option
public String ticksuffix
        Tick label suffix.

      • ticktext

        @Option
public String[] ticktext
        The text displayed at the ticks position via "tickvals". Only has an effect if "tickmode" is set to "array". Used with "tickvals".

      • tickvals

        @Option
public double[] tickvals
        The values at which ticks on this axis appear. Only has an effect if "tickmode" is set to "array". Used with "ticktext".

      • title

        @Option
public String title
        The title of the axis.

      • titlefont

        @Option
public final FontOptions titlefont
        The font of the axis.

      • type

        @Option
public AxisOptions.TypeEnum type
        The axis type. Defaults to AUTO.
